===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|泉|厂|t1=spring|t2=cliff|ls=ic}} – a spring bursting from a cliff-side – origin. A conservative variant is [[厡]], in which water is well visible at the bottom.

===Etymology===
The sense “source, origin; basic, primary” is perhaps related to {{och-l|元|head; principal; first; great}} ({{zh-ref|Qiu, 1988}}). According to {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}}, in {{w|Shijing}} 原 meant "a plain" as well as "highland", thus perhaps also related to {{och-l|元}} (see also {{zh-ref|Qiu, 2000}}).

{{lang|zh|元}} and {{lang|zh|原}} had been used interchangeably in the sense "origin" until {{lang|zh|原}} became favoured in the early {{w|Ming dynasty}} to avoid the name of the {{w|Yuan dynasty}}. Confer {{zh-l|元由}}, {{zh-l|元來}} and {{zh-l|元配}}.<ref>清·郝懿行《晉宋書故·元由》：“今人爲書元俱作原字……葢起於前明初造事涉元朝文字簿書率皆易元爲原沿至今日”</ref>

